  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.relation:from{A}:to{B}]\nDescribes: R\nwhen: A, B is \\set\nextends: R \\:subset:/ \\set.theoretic.cartesian.product:of{A}:and{B}\nEnables:\n. capability: R(a_, b_) :-> (a_, b_) \"in\" R\n  written: \"a_? \\: R \\: b_?\"\nDocumented:\n. called: \"relation from $A?$ to $B?$\"\n. written: \"R? \\subseteq A? \\times B?\"\n. description: \"A relation $R$ from $A$ to $B$ is a subset of $A \\times B$. When $(a, b) \\in R$ one writes $a \\mathbin{R} b$. A relation from $A$ to $A$ is called a relation in $A$.\"\nId: \"982d5d26-08c5-41f7-a22b-68c0434450f0\"",
